events.summary: School of Theatre and Dance Presents "The Father: A Tragic Farce"
events.name: CAL-01f62b63-6de37858-016d-fbbfe610-000028a6.ics
categories: College of Visual & Performing Arts (J.T. & Margaret Talkington)
events.description:
"The Father: A Tragic Farce" by Florian Zeller

An elderly man with dementia, Andre, has been living in the same flat for over thirty years. Accustomed to taking care of himself, he is thrown into chaos when his family and friends tell him how to live his life. The Father is a heartfelt tragicomedy about a family coping with the effects of physical and mental loss, exposing the cost of what it means for one man to maintain his independence.
events.cost: $15 for individuals; $5 for students with valid ID

events.summary: Fulbright U.S. Student Program - Student Info Session
events.name: CAL-01f62b63-6e4aae6e-016e-6b42abab-000074f7.ics

contact.name: National and International Scholarships and Fellowships

events.description:
Join us in the TLPDC 151 (TTU Library) to learn about the Fulbright U.S. Student Program, which provides 8-12 month funding for study, research, or teaching English abroad. Choose from over 140 countries! The grant includes round-trip fare, a monthly stipend, health coverage, and more.

Undergraduates apply during the fall of their senior year.  Graduate students may not earn a Ph.D. before or during grant period.  

** Texas Tech students must follow the internal TTU process to apply.

events.summary: IGNITE! Texas Tech's Program for LGBTQIA Allyship
events.name: CAL-01f62b63-6c69111d-016c-8c6f8850-00007500.ics
events.description: IGNITE! educates on the lived experiences of lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer, intersex, and asexual (LGBTQIA) people, while networking and providing general support to students, faculty, and staff in their development as authentic allies. Program participants commit to act with compassion, respect, and dignity, and engage with others, including the Office of LGBTQIA Education & Engagement, to strengthen the inclusivity of Texas Tech University.

events.name: CAL-01f62b63-6c69111d-016d-5ea18e93-000039a6.ics
events.description: Fifty+ years ago, the term “sexism” was coined. This film series considers ways in which sexism is embedded, endorsed, and/or challenged in the cinema. Together, these films featuring women as central protagonists offer an intriguing site for the analysis of representations of race/ethnicity, femininities, masculinities, socio-economic classes, and sexualities. All movies are screened on the first Wednesday of the month during the school year at the Alamo Drafthouse.

events.name: CAL-01f62b63-6c69111d-016d-69a80b21-00000805.ics
events.description: The multi-platinum, critically-acclaimed progressive rock group announced its highly-anticipated Winter Tour 2019. Returning with all-new staging and effects is the unforgettable show that started it all, “Christmas Eve and Other Stories.” TSO’s show that started small, performed to 12,000 people in five cities in 1999, which then exploded onto the national scene, eventually playing to 9 million fans over the course of an incredible 12 years, the mega-hit “Christmas Eve and Other Stories."

events.summary: 19th Annual High and Dry Photography Exhibit – Opening Reception
events.name: CAL-01f62b63-6e4aae6e-016e-6babdf76-00007850.ics
events.description:
Hosted by the TTU Office of International Affairs: Come celebrate the unique beauty of the world’s arid and semiarid landscapes at the opening reception for the 19th Annual High and Dry Exhibit. This premiere juried photographic exhibition will display the work of fifty-seven local and national photographers. 

This exhibit is made possible in part through a grant from the City of Lubbock, as recommended by Civic Lubbock, Inc. and The CH Foundation.

events.description:
CMA and ACM Award-winning musician Luke Combs will extend his sold-out “Beer Never Broke My Heart Tour” through this fall.

The tour will make its stop at Lubbock's United Supermarkets Arena Friday, December 6, and will feature special guests Morgan Wallen & Jameson Rodgers.

Tickets are priced $57.50, 52.00, $41.25, and $30.25 (inclusive of fees) and are scheduled to go on sale through at www.selectaseatlubbock.com, 806-770-2000, and Lubbock area Select-a-Seat outlets.
